The paper discusses the use of neural networks for function approximation in reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes new activation functions for neural networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of on-policy learning and softmax action selection, which are topics in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper validates its approach by achieving state-of-the-art results in the Atari 2600 domain, which involves computer vision (cs.CV).
